2. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper involves natural language processing (NLP) as it generates scene representations from textual descriptions. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a model that learns to generate scene representations from natural language descriptions, which falls under the domain of AI. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed model uses sequential generation and attention mechanisms, which are common techniques in machine learning. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper deals with generating different forms of scene representations, including cartoon-like scenes and synthetic images, which falls under the domain of graphics.
